org.jcatapult.action.jcatapult
Class States

java.lang.Object
  org.jcatapult.action.jcatapult.States
All Implemented Interfaces:
com.opensymphony.xwork2.Action
public class States
extends Object
implements com.opensymphony.xwork2.Action

This class is a common action that provides a list of the US states in a map where the key of the map is the state code and the value of the map is the state name.

setIncludeTerritories

public void setIncludeTerritories(boolean includeTerritories)
Set to true to include territories in the list of states

Parameters:
includeTerritories - true if including territories, false otherwise

setIncludeBlank

public void setIncludeBlank(boolean includeBlank)
This parameters determines if a blank entry is added to the front of the linked Map that is built by the execute() method. The blank key will always be empty String and the value will default to empty String unless set by the setBlankValue(String) method.

Parameters:
includeBlank - If true a blank will be inserted, false it will not. This defaults to false.

setBlankValue

public void setBlankValue(String blankValue)
This parameter is the value that will be used for the blank spot if the setIncludeBlank(boolean) parameter is set to true. The key will always empty String.

Parameters:
blankValue - The value for the blank spot.

setPreferredStates

public void setPreferredStates(String preferredStates)
This parameter can be passed in in order to set up the states that should be at the top of the Map. These are the state abbreviation codes and the order they are given is the order that they are put into the linked Map.

Parameters:
preferredStates - The preferred state abbreviation codes.

getStates

public Map<String,String> getStates()

The Map or null if execute was not called.
